        <div class="feature-content">
            <div class="cols-3">
                <img src="~/Image/StateImage/WestBengal/kolkata.jpg">
                <h3> Kolkata </h3>
                <p> Kolkata, formerly known as Calcutta, is the educational, commercial and cultural centre of the Eastern part of India, and is the third most populous metropolitan city of India.  </p>
            </div>
            <div class="cols-3">
                <img src="~/Image/StateImage/WestBengal/murshidabad.jpg">
                <h3> Murshidabad </h3>
                <p> The last capital city of independent Bengal before British rule was named after Nawab Murshid Quli Khan, the Dewan of Bengal, Bihar and Orissa. Situated on the banks of the Bhagirathi, it is a city of splendours and is famous for its silk.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="cols-3">
                <img src="~/Image/StateImage/WestBengal/darjeeling.jpg">
                <h3> Darjeeling </h3>
                <p>Darjeeling is famous throughout the world for the tea it grows and the great view of Kanchenjunga range of mountains that it offers. It is also known for its richness in cultural & natural heritage and the famous toy train that has been declared a UN heritage. </p>
            </div>
            <div class="cols-3">
                <img src="~/Image/StateImage/WestBengal/kalimpong.jpg">
                <h3> Kalimpong </h3>
                <p>  If you're planning a tour of Darjeeling or Sikkim, then you should definitely add Kalimpong to your travel itinerary. There is a myriad of exciting things you can do here, like paragliding in Kalimpong and climbing Deolo Hill to take in the scenic views of the mountains. </p>
            </div>
        </div>
