                        <ul class="section-content-list">
                            <li>
                                The land of bookworms Kolkata, or Calcutta, as still lovingly called by the Bengalis, College Street or ‘Boi Para’ (Colony of Books) is the largest book market in India.
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                Largest book fair in Asia and third largest book fair in the world is the Kolkata Book Fair.
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                Contrary to the rickshaws that we ride in several parts of India, these are Calcutta’s own unique rickshaws.
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                The literacy rate of Kolkata is 87.54% according to the Census 2011. This figure is way above the national average of 74.04%.
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                The National Library in Kolkata is the nation’s largest public library.
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </p>
                </div>
